    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3534" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπί - κλησις</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καλέω</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">given name</span>
          (‘surname’); only acc., adverbially or predicatively, mostly with
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καλεῖν, Ἄρκτον θ̓, ἣν καὶ ἅμαξαν ἐπίκλησιν
            καλέουσιν</span>, ‘which they call also <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">by the
            name</span> of the wain,’ <i><span class="en">Od.
          5.273</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 7.138</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 22.506</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; Σπερχειῷ, αὐτὰρ ἐπίκλησιν Βώρῳ</span>, ‘but
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">by repute</span> to B.,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            16.177</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
